Somebody will do them.

02:04.601 --> 02:06.634
[QUIETLY]
Yeah. I wonder
who that somebody is.

02:09.701 --> 02:10.701
I'll see you tonight.

02:10.701 --> 02:12.033
See ya.

02:13.934 --> 02:15.934
Bye, guys.
Have a good day.

02:15.934 --> 02:17.634
Bye.
Bye.

02:22.801 --> 02:24.167
Okay, listen.

02:24.167 --> 02:25.734
I gotta go.
Me too.

02:25.734 --> 02:27.868
Just wait a second.
Oh, I see.

02:27.868 --> 02:29.868
She can't be late.
Us, what's the difference?

02:29.868 --> 02:33.200
Look, I don't know what you
think you're gonna accomplish

02:33.200 --> 02:34.934
with this whole
hostility routine

02:34.934 --> 02:36.267
every time Grace is in the room.

02:36.267 --> 02:38.534
"Yes," "No," "Bye."

02:38.534 --> 02:40.334
Talk to the woman
for God's sake.

02:40.334 --> 02:41.534
What's the matter, Charlie?

02:41.534 --> 02:42.734
It makes you uncomfortable?

02:42.734 --> 02:44.067
It makes her uncomfortable?

02:44.067 --> 02:46.000
My boyfriend isn't even
allowed in the house.

02:47.200 --> 02:49.267
So that's what
this is about. Sam.

02:51.934 --> 02:53.334
Okay. Okay.

02:53.334 --> 02:55.000
You know what? Fine. Whatever.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.200
Bring him here if you want.

02:56.200 --> 02:57.801
I don't want.

03:03.267 --> 03:04.634
Claud,

03:09.300 --> 03:13.501
we can't--
We can't live like this.

03:13.501 --> 03:15.300
It's dumb,
everybody being all pissed off

03:15.300 --> 03:16.901
at each other all the time.

03:16.901 --> 03:20.334
I mean, you don't have anything
against Grace, right?

03:20.334 --> 03:23.834
I think you two could be--
Could be friends.

03:23.834 --> 03:27.601
I mean, things could be--

03:27.601 --> 03:30.467
Things could be pretty good
around here if you just--

03:33.000 --> 03:34.334
Thanks for doing those.

03:45.567 --> 03:49.934
Okay. It's officially too late
for me to get to Psych.

03:49.934 --> 03:51.067
Oh, well.

03:51.067 --> 03:52.834
What are you skipping
this time?

03:52.834 --> 03:54.434
[CHUCKLES]

03:54.434 --> 03:58.234
A lab on stimulus and response.

03:58.234 --> 04:01.701
Hey, you want
to be my study partner?

04:01.701 --> 04:04.534
Mm, sorry. I gotta go.

04:04.534 --> 04:06.300
Where?

04:06.300 --> 04:08.968
Uh, errands, life,

04:08.968 --> 04:10.567
responsibilities.

04:10.567 --> 04:11.667
Remember those?

04:11.667 --> 04:13.534
I gotta go to the Xerox place.

04:13.534 --> 04:16.567
I gotta go to the bank--
Oh, speaking of which.

04:19.500 --> 04:20.434
What?

04:23.400 --> 04:25.000
Oh, rent.

04:25.000 --> 04:26.834
Yes. Hello. Rent.

04:26.834 --> 04:31.133
Could you--? Could you
spot me a couple of days?

04:31.133 --> 04:32.133
[GROANS]

04:32.133 --> 04:33.868
You know,
you did this last month.

04:33.868 --> 04:34.868
I know.

04:34.868 --> 04:37.200
I know. I'm a horrible person,

04:37.200 --> 04:40.834
I just had to get the battery
replaced on my jeep and--

04:40.834 --> 04:43.200
Well, maybe if you stopped
buying rounds for everybody

04:43.200 --> 04:44.567
in every stupid bar you go to...

04:44.567 --> 04:45.801
Give me a break.
I'll--

04:45.801 --> 04:47.901
I'll pay you back, soon.

04:49.167 --> 04:50.367
Okay?
As soon as soon as I can.

04:51.934 --> 04:52.934
Will you?

04:52.934 --> 04:54.534
Do I have a choice?

04:54.534 --> 04:56.434
Is that a "yes"?

04:57.767 --> 05:00.067
Until the end of week.
That's it.

05:00.067 --> 05:01.601
You rule, Cal,
you out and out rule.

05:01.601 --> 05:03.033
Has anybody ever told you--?

05:03.033 --> 05:05.334
No. You know what? Just don't
get used to this, okay?

05:05.334 --> 05:06.834
Just 'cause you sleep
in my room now

05:06.834 --> 05:08.400
doesn't mean you're being kept.

05:15.634 --> 05:17.767
[CHATTER]

05:17.767 --> 05:19.434
Sarah, hey.

05:19.434 --> 05:21.133
Hey.

05:21.133 --> 05:22.434
Good. You made it.

05:22.434 --> 05:24.234
You know, I thought
I was gonna be so early,

05:24.234 --> 05:26.234
but I guess everyone else
thought that too, huh?

05:26.234 --> 05:27.534
Yeah.

05:27.534 --> 05:29.434
So you know what,
I-I didn't want you to worry

05:29.434 --> 05:31.767
or think that I was--
I was blowing you off,

05:31.767 --> 05:35.968
or anything, but I-- I think
I'm gonna, um, skip tonight.

05:35.968 --> 05:37.133
Take Sam.

05:37.133 --> 05:39.434
What? Why?

05:39.434 --> 05:42.801
You're not still mad at me about
the Stanford stuff, are you?

05:42.801 --> 05:44.667
'Cause I thought we were--
No, I'm not. No.

05:44.667 --> 05:47.133
It's just, God, you know,
one love song too many,

05:47.133 --> 05:49.033
and you're gonna need, like,
a giant spatula

05:49.033 --> 05:50.367
to scrape me off the floor.

05:50.367 --> 05:52.234
Come on, you can't
stay home all the time.

05:52.234 --> 05:53.968
Why not?

05:55.467 --> 05:56.667
You miss him, huh?

05:56.667 --> 05:58.000
No.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.167
No.

05:59.167 --> 06:02.567
It's just--
I just wish I didn't.

06:03.667 --> 06:05.834
Well, maybe you should call him?
Right.

06:05.834 --> 06:08.133
So she can answer the phone?
No, I am not gonna call him.

06:08.133 --> 06:09.334
I broke up with him,

06:09.334 --> 06:12.300
and the person that breaks up
doesn't call.

06:12.300 --> 06:15.200
Besides, you know,
if he were thinking about me,

06:15.200 --> 06:20.901
or he missed me,
which obviously he doesn't,

06:20.901 --> 06:23.834
you know, he--
He could find me.

06:23.834 --> 06:27.000
So you're saying
you'd want to hear from him?

06:27.000 --> 06:28.567
Wow, the line's moving.

06:31.834 --> 06:33.968
How's it going?

06:33.968 --> 06:36.267
How are things with--
I don't know.

06:36.267 --> 06:40.067
--school and wrestling
and Callie?

06:40.067 --> 06:41.801
Not now about Callie. Okay?

06:45.300 --> 06:47.400
What are you looking for?

06:47.400 --> 06:50.000
Those old stereo speakers I had.

06:51.100 --> 06:52.968
Are you okay, Bay?

06:52.968 --> 06:55.667
You look a little puffy
and kind of tired.

06:55.667 --> 06:56.701
Wow.

06:56.701 --> 06:58.400
I should stop by more often.

06:58.400 --> 07:00.000
Well, I'm sorry, but you do.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.133
Well,
I haven't been sleeping great.

07:02.133 --> 07:05.834
Yeah, well, between studying
and practice and--

07:07.334 --> 07:09.267
I don't know, maybe it's because
you miss Sarah.

07:11.367 --> 07:12.634
You know what, Julia?

07:12.634 --> 07:14.601
You didn't butt into our
relationship before,

07:14.601 --> 07:16.033
now's not a good time
to start.

07:16.033 --> 07:17.868
Aha.

07:17.868 --> 07:19.033
There you are.

07:20.167 --> 07:21.701
The other ones
finally keel over?

07:21.701 --> 07:23.534
Too muchPearl Jam?
No.

07:23.534 --> 07:24.701
I'm selling these.

07:26.767 --> 07:28.801
Hey, you wouldn't happen to have

07:28.801 --> 07:30.434
any spare cash lying around,
would you?

07:31.868 --> 07:34.634
Well, I've got like, uh,

07:34.634 --> 07:37.000
50 bucks I could lend you.

07:37.000 --> 07:38.200
Is that enough?

07:38.200 --> 07:39.868
No, but I'll take it.

07:39.868 --> 07:41.601
Why are you so broke?

07:41.601 --> 07:45.901
Because--
Because that class I dropped,

07:45.901 --> 07:48.567
they didn't buy the books back,

07:48.567 --> 07:50.901
and the alternator went
on my jeep last week,

07:50.901 --> 07:52.734
and I don't know,

07:52.734 --> 07:55.567
basically this past month
just kind of sucked.

07:55.567 --> 07:58.901
Well, here. Take this too.

08:00.267 --> 08:01.501
"Burn and Groove."

08:01.501 --> 08:03.200
They're playing tonight.

08:03.200 --> 08:04.701
You got an extra?

08:04.701 --> 08:07.467
Yeah. Yeah.
Meet me there. It'll be fun.

08:14.634 --> 08:15.968
Claudia.

08:15.968 --> 08:17.634
Hi.

08:17.634 --> 08:20.367
Wow. This--
This is a nice office.

08:20.367 --> 08:22.133
I didn't think it had
this many windows.

08:22.133 --> 08:23.534
You want one?

08:23.534 --> 08:26.634
The guy was selling these
right where I got off the bus.

08:26.634 --> 08:27.901
What are you doing here?

08:27.901 --> 08:29.801
You know, visiting.

08:31.200 --> 08:33.868
And I was, um, thinking,
you know,

08:33.868 --> 08:35.701
maybe I could volunteer

08:36.701 --> 08:39.933
to work for you.

08:39.933 --> 08:41.833
Hold it. Hold it.
[PHONE RINGING]

08:41.833 --> 08:43.634
Your brother told you
to do this, right?

08:43.634 --> 08:46.100
No. Call him.

08:46.100 --> 08:47.467
Check.

08:49.000 --> 08:51.300
Harvest Program.
This is Grace.

08:52.334 --> 08:53.968
Oh. Oh, good,
I was waiting for--

08:53.968 --> 08:55.634
Let me write this-- Hang on.

08:59.667 --> 09:02.000
Okay.
The fax number is--

09:07.434 --> 09:08.934
Okay. Great.

09:08.934 --> 09:12.067
We'll have that proposal
to you by the end of week.

09:12.067 --> 09:13.200
Thanks.

09:14.834 --> 09:15.834
Thanks.

09:15.834 --> 09:17.868
No problem.

09:17.868 --> 09:20.334
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

09:30.934 --> 09:31.934
Sarah.

09:33.400 --> 09:34.501
Hi.

09:34.501 --> 09:35.634
Hey.

09:35.634 --> 09:39.501
I was, um, I was--
I was meeting Julia.

09:39.501 --> 09:40.434
Me too.

09:42.234 --> 09:43.634
Did she give you her ticket?

09:43.634 --> 09:45.701
She said it was an extra.

09:45.701 --> 09:47.634
It was hers.

09:49.300 --> 09:51.501
God, like it was up to her--

09:51.501 --> 09:52.968
No kidding.

09:52.968 --> 09:53.968
I'll go.

09:53.968 --> 09:55.901
No. You know what?
You know what?

09:55.901 --> 09:58.067
You stay. I'll go.

09:58.067 --> 09:59.501
No, I mean,
it wasn't your fault.

10:00.934 --> 10:02.300
Maybe we--
You know what--

10:02.300 --> 10:04.434
[BOTH CHUCKLE NERVOUSLY]

10:04.434 --> 10:05.734
Go ahead.

10:05.734 --> 10:10.133
Uh, I was just gonna say,
we're already here,

10:10.133 --> 10:12.133
so maybe we so could just--

10:12.133 --> 10:13.133
Yeah.

10:13.133 --> 10:14.200
Yeah, okay.
Yeah?

10:14.200 --> 10:15.200
Yeah.

10:24.701 --> 10:26.334
I'm still gonna kill her.

10:26.334 --> 10:27.601
Me too.

10:27.601 --> 10:29.434
She's got a lot of nerve
doing this.

10:32.501 --> 10:35.868
So Claudia says you got her
doing computer inputting.

10:35.868 --> 10:37.100
Two months from now

10:37.100 --> 10:38.901
she'll probably
be running the place.

10:38.901 --> 10:39.901
Heh. Could be.

10:39.901 --> 10:41.200
So that's good.

10:41.200 --> 10:43.267
That's a good sign,
her wanting to work with you.

10:43.267 --> 10:44.868
I knew it would just take some
time to--

10:44.868 --> 10:46.000
I'm sorry.

10:46.000 --> 10:47.767
Are you doing
a taste test or something?

10:47.767 --> 10:49.033
No. We're just a--

10:49.033 --> 10:51.667
A family with very specific
pretzel preferences:

10:51.667 --> 10:53.601
Claudia, salted,
Julia, unsalted,

10:53.601 --> 10:54.601
and me, honey mustard.

10:54.601 --> 10:56.400
[GROANS]

10:56.400 --> 10:57.567
No offense.

10:57.567 --> 10:59.067
None taken.

10:59.067 --> 11:01.734
So you know I'm only chipping
in for the healthy stuff, right?

11:01.734 --> 11:04.434
Forget it.
You're not paying for any of it.

11:04.434 --> 11:06.601
Oh, shoot.
I forgot his juice boxes.

11:06.601 --> 11:08.200
I'm sorry, buddy.
I'll be right back.

11:08.200 --> 11:11.601
WOMAN [ON PA]:
 <i>Produce manager,</i>
 <i>pick up line 1.</i>

11:11.601 --> 11:13.534
No, sweetie.
No gum today.

11:13.534 --> 11:16.000
Of course they put the candy
and gum and toys right up front

11:16.000 --> 11:17.767
where you're practically
held hostage.

11:17.767 --> 11:19.767
I never thought about that.

11:19.767 --> 11:21.534
Well.

11:21.534 --> 11:22.968
Oh, he's cute.

11:22.968 --> 11:24.033
Is he three?

11:24.033 --> 11:25.067
Almost.

11:25.067 --> 11:27.300
He looks very well
taken care of.

11:27.300 --> 11:28.300
I guess so.

11:28.300 --> 11:29.701
Can I ask you,

11:29.701 --> 11:31.400
my girl left a few days ago.

11:31.400 --> 11:33.767
Family emergency in Haiti,
Jamaica, I don't--

11:33.767 --> 11:34.901
I need somebody.

11:34.901 --> 11:37.133
Do you know of anyone
who's looking?

11:37.133 --> 11:38.501
I'm not trying to steal you.

11:38.501 --> 11:42.067
I meant any of your friends or--
I'm not his nanny.

11:42.067 --> 11:44.167
Oh.

11:44.167 --> 11:45.934
Oh, I'm--
That's okay.

11:45.934 --> 11:48.033
I'm sorry. I didn't--
It's okay.

11:51.601 --> 11:53.467
[BAND PLAYING ROCK SONG]

12:00.434 --> 12:01.501
SINGER:
Thanks a lot.

12:01.501 --> 12:03.200
We're gonna take
a short intermission.

12:03.200 --> 12:04.434
Back in 15.

12:08.334 --> 12:10.567
Well, they suck.

12:11.801 --> 12:13.634
What?

12:13.634 --> 12:16.534
I'm just expressing an opinion.

12:16.534 --> 12:18.701
I guess if you got 10
fingers and some attitude,

12:18.701 --> 12:20.367
you can call yourself
a guitar player.

12:20.367 --> 12:22.000
What a rip-off.

12:22.000 --> 12:23.434
Am I right?

12:24.434 --> 12:25.634
[SCOFFS]

12:25.634 --> 12:27.968
Great.
Bunch of pods.

12:27.968 --> 12:29.534
You know,
I thought they were great,

12:29.534 --> 12:31.634
and I don't know what
you're complaining about,

12:31.634 --> 12:33.133
you didn't even pay
for the ticket.

12:33.133 --> 12:34.467
Whoa.

12:34.467 --> 12:36.634
What are you getting
so defensive for, Sarah?

12:36.634 --> 12:38.200
I'm not.
I was just saying--

12:38.200 --> 12:39.634
What--? What, are you sleeping

12:39.634 --> 12:41.601
with one of the guys
in the band? Is that it?

12:41.601 --> 12:42.968
What?

12:42.968 --> 12:44.400
God, what is with you?

12:44.400 --> 12:47.100
Nothing. Nothing.

12:47.100 --> 12:49.133
I'm just--
I'm just making conversation.

12:49.133 --> 12:50.400
I'm just catching up.

12:53.234 --> 12:54.501
That one guy, the--

12:54.501 --> 12:56.901
The bald guy, he'd be a good
boyfriend for you.

12:56.901 --> 12:58.167
Cut it out.

12:58.167 --> 12:59.400
I can go talk to him.

12:59.400 --> 13:00.734
I could go backstage

13:00.734 --> 13:02.501
and give him your phone number.
Stop it.

13:02.501 --> 13:04.701
Hey, I just want you
to be happy, Sarah.

13:04.701 --> 13:06.601
You want that?
You want me to be happy?

13:06.601 --> 13:08.267
Yeah.
Okay.

13:08.267 --> 13:10.267
Hey, hey, where are you--?

13:23.734 --> 13:25.734
* Mock *
* Yeah *

13:25.734 --> 13:27.767
* --ing *
* Yeah *

13:27.767 --> 13:29.701
* --bird *
SINGER [ON RADIO]: * <i>Yeah *</i>

13:29.701 --> 13:31.767
[LAUGHING]
* Yeah *
 <i>* Yeah *</i>

13:31.767 --> 13:33.133
What are you laughing at?

13:33.133 --> 13:35.033
You. Don't take this
the wrong way,

13:35.033 --> 13:36.968
but you should not quit
your day job.

13:36.968 --> 13:39.834
Oh, gee, don't start.
I wish I could.

13:39.834 --> 13:41.167
Why?
What's the matter?

13:41.167 --> 13:42.601
Oh, I just got three jobs,

13:42.601 --> 13:44.200
supposed to be finished
yesterday.

13:44.200 --> 13:46.000
Two guys out with the flu.

13:46.000 --> 13:47.868
Really?
Mm.

13:47.868 --> 13:49.434
Well, maybe you could
use some help.

13:49.434 --> 13:50.868
I might know someone.

13:50.868 --> 13:54.100
Sweetheart, sexy as I think
you'd look in coveralls--

13:54.100 --> 13:55.334
No, no, no. Not me.

13:55.334 --> 13:57.267
I was thinking Bailey could do
work for you.

13:57.267 --> 13:58.968
Bailey?
Yeah.

13:58.968 --> 14:00.734
Yeah. I mean, he could really
use the money

14:00.734 --> 14:04.000
and, you know, he could meet you
in between classes or after,

14:04.000 --> 14:06.133
and he's completely
reliable and responsible.

14:06.133 --> 14:08.133
It would be like hiring
a boy scout.

14:08.133 --> 14:09.801
Plus he has excellent
references.

14:09.801 --> 14:11.634
You mean, besides you?

14:12.734 --> 14:13.901
That's a joke.

14:13.901 --> 14:15.000
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

14:15.000 --> 14:17.367
Yeah, yeah.
Go ahead and ask him.

14:17.367 --> 14:18.834
Okay.

14:18.834 --> 14:22.067
* Bird won't sing
You're gonna buy yourself *

14:22.067 --> 14:23.334
* Buy yourself a diamond ring *

14:23.334 --> 14:24.801
JULIA:
Stop.

14:24.801 --> 14:26.834
[***]

14:29.334 --> 14:31.067
Ow.

14:31.067 --> 14:32.067
Charlie.

14:32.067 --> 14:34.501
Hm? What?

14:34.501 --> 14:37.334
Mm, what time is it?

14:37.334 --> 14:40.033
Early.

14:40.033 --> 14:42.234
Mm. Yeah.

14:42.234 --> 14:43.767
Charlie, wait.

14:45.968 --> 14:48.234
I don't think this
is the best idea.

14:48.234 --> 14:50.300
Him, here.

14:52.234 --> 14:53.767
What's the big deal?

14:53.767 --> 14:55.868
Didn't you ever climb
into bed with your parents?

14:55.868 --> 14:57.834
I'm not his parent.

14:57.834 --> 15:00.567
I'm not his step-parent,
not even close.

15:02.767 --> 15:05.067
But I think
he kind of needs this,

15:05.067 --> 15:06.767
to cuddle with me
every once in a while.

15:06.767 --> 15:09.767
Not every night, but sometimes.

15:09.767 --> 15:11.934
What am I supposed to do?
Kick him out?

15:11.934 --> 15:13.667
Not sleep with you?

15:13.667 --> 15:15.834
I'm sorry.
I know, you think I'm--

15:15.834 --> 15:19.367
I just--
I feel really uncomfortable.

15:21.267 --> 15:23.501
Okay, okay.

15:23.501 --> 15:24.801
I'll take him back to his room.

15:28.868 --> 15:30.767
He has more of a right
to be here than I do.

15:30.767 --> 15:32.968
What?

15:32.968 --> 15:34.801
Nothing.

15:34.801 --> 15:37.501
Look, I'm gonna take him,
put him back in his room,

15:37.501 --> 15:39.634
and I'm gonna go
and make you a cup of coffee.

15:39.634 --> 15:41.901
I didn't realize you get
so snarky in the morning.

15:41.901 --> 15:43.801
[DISTANT CAR STARTS]

15:45.234 --> 15:46.901
[SIGHS]

15:46.901 --> 15:48.367
[BELL RINGING]

15:51.734 --> 15:54.033
Okay, you know what? First
of all, don't ever set me up

15:54.033 --> 15:55.834
like that again ever.
Sarah--

15:55.834 --> 15:58.000
I didn't ask you to,
and I didn't want you to.

15:58.000 --> 15:59.601
All right. I was just trying to
be nice.

15:59.601 --> 16:00.601
I know.
But it wasn't.

16:00.601 --> 16:02.701
Well, I'm sorry.

16:02.701 --> 16:04.100
That doesn't help.

16:04.100 --> 16:08.300
You-- You have no idea
how bad it was.

16:08.300 --> 16:11.667
Maybe you haven't spent that
much time with him lately,

16:11.667 --> 16:13.734
but he's--
God, he's really a mess.

16:13.734 --> 16:15.934
What does that mean, "a mess"?

16:15.934 --> 16:18.234
I mean, I know he's been unhappy
since you guys broke up.

16:18.234 --> 16:19.901
Maybe he's just taking
it really hard?

16:19.901 --> 16:23.734
Julia, this isn't that. Okay?
He was drunk and loud--

16:23.734 --> 16:25.267
Whoa, whoa, wait.
It was a concert.

16:25.267 --> 16:27.667
Everybody drinks
and everybody's loud.

16:27.667 --> 16:29.033
Not the way he was.

16:29.033 --> 16:31.567
Well, maybe he was just nervous
seeing you.

16:31.567 --> 16:33.133
I'd understand that.

16:33.133 --> 16:35.434
This isn't the first time
he's acted this way, Julia.

16:35.434 --> 16:37.300
Okay? Even Will noticed
it when he was here.

16:37.300 --> 16:39.901
Noticed what?
What I'm telling you. Okay?

16:39.901 --> 16:41.767
He drinks all the time now.

16:41.767 --> 16:43.968
How do you know what he does
all the time?

16:43.968 --> 16:45.501
You're never around him.

16:48.868 --> 16:50.701
Okay. Look, you know, I--

16:50.701 --> 16:53.467
I know that he's your big
brother and everything,

16:53.467 --> 16:55.734
and maybe you need to keep him
on some kind of pedestal,

16:55.734 --> 16:57.734
but there's something--
Hey, I know Bailey

16:57.734 --> 16:59.734
better than you do.
And you're wrong.

16:59.734 --> 17:01.100
Fine.

17:01.100 --> 17:02.167
Great. Great.

17:02.167 --> 17:03.167
You know what?

17:03.167 --> 17:04.166
You're right.

17:04.166 --> 17:05.434
He doesn't have a problem.

17:05.434 --> 17:06.701
I have a problem.

17:06.701 --> 17:08.367
And-- And you know what?
I'm done.

17:08.367 --> 17:11.133
This time I mean it.
I am done. Problem solved.

17:24.767 --> 17:27.267
Sam, sorry, man.

17:27.267 --> 17:29.567
I thought you said
a left on Pine.

17:29.567 --> 17:32.200
And then there's this detour,
you know, go three miles

17:32.200 --> 17:34.400
in some huge circle out
of your way instead of 10 feet

17:34.400 --> 17:36.100
straight ahead.

17:36.100 --> 17:37.901
Anyway--
Anyway, it's not your concern.

17:37.901 --> 17:40.467
So, what have we got going here?
What's the deal?

17:40.467 --> 17:42.567
They're having a wedding
reception this weekend,

17:42.567 --> 17:44.434
and the daughter's first fiancé,

17:44.434 --> 17:46.334
who she didn't marry,

17:46.334 --> 17:50.200
they-- They bought the wallpaper
from his parents.

17:50.200 --> 17:52.334
Anyway, she decides yesterday

17:52.334 --> 17:54.000
that it would be unlucky
or something.

17:54.000 --> 17:55.701
I don't know.

17:55.701 --> 17:56.868
Man, you gotta love people.

17:56.868 --> 17:57.901
You gotta love them.

17:59.868 --> 18:02.133
Anyway, I need you
to, uh, prime the walls,

18:02.133 --> 18:04.167
and then we'll
put a coat of paint on.

18:04.167 --> 18:05.200
I'm prime to prime.

18:06.467 --> 18:07.667
Whoa.
Sorry.

18:07.667 --> 18:09.300
Sorry. Accident.

18:12.767 --> 18:14.367
I gotta check on a job
in the Haight.

18:15.367 --> 18:16.300
Then I'll be back.

18:17.801 --> 18:19.868
Pete's working in the yard
if you need anything.

18:19.868 --> 18:23.567
No sweat. I'm here,
I'm yours, and I aim to please.

18:23.567 --> 18:26.534
And-- And-- Listen, Sam,
I really appreciate this.

18:26.534 --> 18:27.968
The--

18:27.968 --> 18:29.567
What do you call it?

18:29.567 --> 18:31.934
The fan belt snapped
in my jeep last week.

18:31.934 --> 18:33.701
It cost me a fortune.

18:33.701 --> 18:36.067
Bailey,

18:36.067 --> 18:37.167
that's not--

18:39.334 --> 18:40.467
That's paint.

18:42.901 --> 18:43.968
I knew that.

18:57.901 --> 19:00.901
Oh. That should be a D.

19:00.901 --> 19:02.834
Oh. Okay.

19:02.834 --> 19:04.601
[BEEPS]

19:04.601 --> 19:08.067
You don't think they'd deliver
it to "Oaklanp," California?

19:08.067 --> 19:10.400
Just be careful.

19:10.400 --> 19:11.434
You know, my--

19:11.434 --> 19:13.300
My fingers are getting
kind of crampy.

19:13.300 --> 19:15.300
I'm usually not
a keyboard person.

19:15.300 --> 19:18.801
Maybe we could, you know,
go get a soda or something?

19:18.801 --> 19:20.767
Why don't you work
on these for now?

19:20.767 --> 19:23.801
Fold them in thirds
and put them in the envelopes.

19:23.801 --> 19:25.701
Okay.

19:40.567 --> 19:43.267
Charlie's totally
crazy about you.

19:46.300 --> 19:49.167
Did you know right away
that you liked him?

19:49.167 --> 19:51.868
Well, 'cause I've always thought
he has that kind of personality

19:51.868 --> 19:53.300
that really needs
to grow on you.

19:53.300 --> 19:55.133
Claudia, I'm working.

19:55.133 --> 19:56.133
So are you.

19:56.133 --> 19:57.801
Oh, yeah.

19:57.801 --> 19:59.834
Sorry.

20:03.000 --> 20:05.033
I think we're getting
Chinese tonight.

20:05.033 --> 20:06.200
What do you like?

20:06.200 --> 20:07.767
MAN:
Hey, you.

20:07.767 --> 20:12.033
Eddie, oh. How have you been?

20:12.033 --> 20:13.801
Everything, huh?

20:13.801 --> 20:14.801
Yep, gone.

20:14.801 --> 20:16.000
Whole apartment just ashes.

20:16.000 --> 20:18.400
Did you find a place yet?

20:18.400 --> 20:20.601
I'm staying with a friend.

20:20.601 --> 20:22.701
In the neighborhood?
'Cause I haven't seen you--

20:22.701 --> 20:23.868
Not too far. Just for now,

20:23.868 --> 20:25.767
you know,
until everything settles.

20:25.767 --> 20:27.868
Hey, you got time for a cup
of coffee or something?

20:27.868 --> 20:29.734
Sure, that'd be great.

20:31.701 --> 20:33.133
[***]

20:41.501 --> 20:44.067
And I figured you were too tired
to stop and get us dinner,

20:44.067 --> 20:46.133
so I got us some really gross
tacos and stuff,

20:46.133 --> 20:48.434
which will be an interesting
test of our relationship,

20:48.434 --> 20:49.701
come to think of it.

20:54.801 --> 20:56.534
You okay?

20:58.734 --> 21:00.300
Yeah, something kind of weird

21:00.300 --> 21:02.667
happened at one
of my job sites today.

21:04.167 --> 21:05.367
Some stuff was ripped-off.

21:05.367 --> 21:08.133
A couple bottles of pretty
expensive liquor.

21:08.133 --> 21:11.601
Man, the people are pissed.

21:11.601 --> 21:13.434
Oh, no. Wow.
Which--? Which job?

21:16.767 --> 21:19.367
Look, I--
I'm not saying Bailey did it...

21:20.734 --> 21:22.801
Well, of course he didn't.
Why would you even--?

21:22.801 --> 21:24.667
I know. I know.

21:26.834 --> 21:28.701
Except Pete,
the other guy who was there,

21:28.701 --> 21:31.300
I called him
and asked him point-blank.

21:31.300 --> 21:33.267
Yeah. And?

21:33.267 --> 21:35.334
And he was outside
the whole time.

21:37.200 --> 21:39.801
He said his boots
were so muddy he never went in.

21:43.067 --> 21:46.000
So I-I-I don't--
I don't know what to think.

21:47.067 --> 21:50.000
So you tell me.

21:50.934 --> 21:53.167
Is it possible?

21:53.167 --> 21:55.634
[***]

22:03.334 --> 22:04.801
[BEEPS]

22:04.801 --> 22:07.100
Hi. No one's here right now,
but you can leave a message

22:07.100 --> 22:11.033
for Charlie, Julia, Claudia,
Owen, and Grace at--

22:11.033 --> 22:13.033
[DOG BARKS]
Shoot.

22:13.033 --> 22:14.734
Claudia.

22:14.734 --> 22:17.033
He barked, not me.

22:17.033 --> 22:19.601
What are you doing?

22:19.601 --> 22:21.267
Putting Grace's name
on this thing.

22:22.868 --> 22:23.934
Really?

22:23.934 --> 22:26.267
Does she want her name
on that thing?

22:26.267 --> 22:29.033
I mean,
did she ask you to do this?

22:29.033 --> 22:31.267
What is your problem?
Are you trying to make trouble?

22:33.367 --> 22:35.501
No.

22:37.334 --> 22:39.200
It's nothing.

22:44.400 --> 22:46.133
Hi.
No one's here right now,

22:46.133 --> 22:49.067
but you can leave a message
for Charlie, Julia, Claudia,

22:49.067 --> 22:50.567
Owen, and Grace at the tone.

22:57.200 --> 22:58.567
[***]

23:01.901 --> 23:03.234
[BELL RINGING]

23:09.434 --> 23:12.100
So?
What are we gonna do about him?

23:12.100 --> 23:14.300
 <i>[PHONE RINGING]</i>

23:14.300 --> 23:17.133
No, no. Wait.
I have the report right, uh--

23:17.133 --> 23:18.767
Give me two seconds here.

23:21.400 --> 23:23.200
What?
I-- I'm sorry, Sandy.

23:23.200 --> 23:25.234
I'm gonna have to call
you back in a bit.

23:28.133 --> 23:30.434
What are these doing here?

23:31.901 --> 23:34.200
I don't know.
What are they doing?

23:34.200 --> 23:36.767
This is page two
of the mailer we're sending.

23:36.767 --> 23:39.033
All those envelopes
you did yesterday?

23:39.033 --> 23:41.300
You didn't tell me there was
more than one page.

23:41.300 --> 23:42.667
What did these look like to you?

23:42.667 --> 23:45.567
What does it say
right here? Page two.

23:45.567 --> 23:48.300
You didn't mail them yet?
No.

23:48.300 --> 23:50.968
Then I'll just unstuff them
and--

23:50.968 --> 23:53.033
We're gonna have to get new
envelopes printed up.

23:53.033 --> 23:56.934
We can't reuse these.
They'll look like garbage.

23:56.934 --> 24:00.334
Oh, God, you already
stamped them, didn't you?

24:00.334 --> 24:01.834
You said to.

24:01.834 --> 24:04.234
You know what? You shouldn't
just jump into something

24:04.234 --> 24:06.400
if you're not sure
if you can handle it.

24:06.400 --> 24:07.968
Wait w--?
What are you trying--?

24:07.968 --> 24:09.067
You--

24:10.033 --> 24:11.734
You can't do sloppy work here.

24:11.734 --> 24:13.000
Hey, I'm a volunteer.

24:13.000 --> 24:14.667
I mean,
I'm doing you a favor here.

24:14.667 --> 24:16.501
You don't have to--
Are you serious?

24:16.501 --> 24:18.033
That's no excuse.

24:18.033 --> 24:20.634
You know what, Claudia?

24:20.634 --> 24:22.567
This is not the appropriate
place for you.

24:22.567 --> 24:23.667
What?

24:23.667 --> 24:24.934
You should go.

24:26.300 --> 24:29.367
Whoa. I mean, I came all the way
down here, two buses,

24:29.367 --> 24:33.400
I live with you,
and you're firing me?

24:33.400 --> 24:35.234
Yes, I am.

24:45.834 --> 24:47.467
What are you doing
home so early?

24:47.467 --> 24:49.133
And why didn't
you come home with Grace?

24:50.300 --> 24:51.701
Ask her.

24:51.701 --> 24:53.367
She fired me.

24:53.367 --> 24:54.934
What'd you do?

24:54.934 --> 24:57.667
Oh, good. Great.
Take her side.

24:57.667 --> 24:59.968
No, who's taking sides?
Excuse me?

24:59.968 --> 25:02.167
I'm just getting a little tired
of every time her name

25:02.167 --> 25:03.634
is mentioned there's a thing.

25:03.634 --> 25:05.968
I'll never mention
her name again.

25:05.968 --> 25:07.000
Does that work for you?

25:07.000 --> 25:09.200
No, Claudia, it doesn't.

25:09.200 --> 25:11.033
Look, this is the way it is.

25:11.033 --> 25:12.734
So--
So get used to it.

25:12.734 --> 25:15.767
Grace lives here now.
She lives here.

25:15.767 --> 25:16.968
Not according to her.

25:16.968 --> 25:18.801
What?
What are you talking about?

25:18.801 --> 25:22.400
She was very busy telling some
guy who came into the place

25:22.400 --> 25:26.434
that she was staying
with friends

25:26.434 --> 25:28.400
temporarily.

25:28.400 --> 25:31.968
Temporarily? That--

25:31.968 --> 25:35.567
Why would she--?
That doesn't make sense.

25:35.567 --> 25:38.400
Fine.

25:38.400 --> 25:40.300
I made it up.

25:43.400 --> 25:46.000
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
Are you accusing me here?

25:46.000 --> 25:47.501
I'm asking you.

25:47.501 --> 25:49.367
Do you know anything
about what happened?

25:49.367 --> 25:51.901
I painted that wall,
and then I split.

25:51.901 --> 25:53.534
You didn't notice
the bottles?

25:53.534 --> 25:55.701
You didn't see anything?

25:55.701 --> 25:58.868
Oh. Oh, yeah. I-I forgot
to mention this.

25:58.868 --> 26:01.467
There was this gang of looters
who broke in after you left.

26:01.467 --> 26:03.000
I tried to fight 'em off,
but--

26:03.000 --> 26:04.534
A simple yes or no.

26:04.534 --> 26:06.667
Who the hell do you think
you are, huh?

26:06.667 --> 26:08.701
Going around
blaming people like this?

26:08.701 --> 26:10.968
Say no,
and the conversation's over.

26:10.968 --> 26:12.767
You know what, Sam?
I'll tell you what.

26:12.767 --> 26:14.067
It's over anyway.

26:17.100 --> 26:18.667
You gonna eat?

26:18.667 --> 26:21.868
Hey, finish that or no
 <i>Bananas in Pyjamas.</i>

26:24.033 --> 26:26.367
Hi, how was your day?

26:26.367 --> 26:28.868
About eight hours
too long.

26:28.868 --> 26:31.801
Did you get those, uh,
change of address cards yet?

26:31.801 --> 26:33.067
Not yet.

26:33.067 --> 26:35.033
Did you remember to call
the phone company

26:35.033 --> 26:37.000
about forwarding
your number here?

26:37.000 --> 26:39.300
What is this?
A welcome-home quiz?

26:40.300 --> 26:43.334
Yes.

26:43.334 --> 26:45.501
Um,

26:47.701 --> 26:48.934
[SIGHS]

26:48.934 --> 26:52.067
are you not planning
on staying here?

26:52.067 --> 26:55.033
'Cause Claud said she--
She heard you tell somebody

26:55.033 --> 26:57.801
that it was temporary.

26:57.801 --> 26:59.701
OWEN:
All done.

26:59.701 --> 27:02.300
Good.
Go, uh-- Go watch your tape.

27:05.334 --> 27:09.033
Are you staying?

27:09.033 --> 27:11.400
We rushed this.
We didn't think.

27:11.400 --> 27:12.901
Um, if the fire hadn't happen--

27:12.901 --> 27:14.767
Yeah, well,
something horrible happened,

27:14.767 --> 27:16.133
we made something
good from it.

27:16.133 --> 27:17.834
What's the matter with that?
No. Look,

27:17.834 --> 27:20.601
I don't belong here,
in this neighborhood,

27:20.601 --> 27:22.300
in this house.
Yes, you do.

27:22.300 --> 27:24.400
Sure, you do.
Right.

27:24.400 --> 27:25.701
I get up in the morning,

27:25.701 --> 27:27.567
your brother's trying
to kick me out of bed.

27:27.567 --> 27:29.868
And your sisters
are giving me the evil eye.

27:29.868 --> 27:31.400
People are thinking
I'm the help.

27:31.400 --> 27:33.267
What?
And then I go into the office,

27:33.267 --> 27:35.567
and all day long I'm dealing
with all these poor people.

27:35.567 --> 27:38.100
Except I feel like
I've crawled under barbed wire,

27:38.100 --> 27:40.100
and I'm just waving at them
from the other side.

27:40.100 --> 27:42.167
La-di-da! Look at me.
With all these white people

27:42.167 --> 27:45.234
and their big expensive houses.
And guess what, kids? It's free.

27:45.234 --> 27:49.868
That is so--
What did you do that's so wrong?

27:49.868 --> 27:52.234
You moved in with
your boyfriend

27:52.234 --> 27:54.300
who happens to be white
and who happens to live

27:54.300 --> 27:57.033
in a pretty decent house.
So what?

27:57.033 --> 27:59.434
I sold out.
Why? Because you're not

27:59.434 --> 28:01.100
ducking drive-bys every minute?

28:01.100 --> 28:03.234
OWEN:
It broke.

28:03.234 --> 28:06.801
Owen, not now.
Go watch something else.

28:08.334 --> 28:09.634
Go!

28:11.501 --> 28:13.033
That's good, Charlie,
yell at him.

28:13.033 --> 28:14.934
That'll definitely make him
like me more.

28:14.934 --> 28:19.067
Man, Grace, what--?
What is this about?

28:19.067 --> 28:20.434
Is this about the--?
The kids?

28:20.434 --> 28:21.767
Is it about the house?

28:21.767 --> 28:23.234
Is it about me?

28:24.300 --> 28:26.534
It's everything.

28:30.834 --> 28:34.634
I-- I don't know how
to solve everything.

28:34.634 --> 28:36.801
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

28:36.801 --> 28:38.968
Whatever you're selling,
I don't want any.

28:38.968 --> 28:41.834
JULIA:
I wanna talk to you.
Open the door.

28:43.300 --> 28:45.601
What?
Let us in.

28:45.601 --> 28:47.567
Us?
Now.

28:52.701 --> 28:55.968
What? Did your boyfriend
send you to search the place?

28:55.968 --> 28:59.601
No. No one sent us.

28:59.601 --> 29:01.334
Bay, what is up?

29:01.334 --> 29:02.634
What is going on with you?

29:02.634 --> 29:04.534
Nothing.

29:04.534 --> 29:06.601
Nothing.
Just leave me alone.

29:06.601 --> 29:07.868
We're worried
about you.

29:07.868 --> 29:10.200
Oh, you two are like
a team on this?

29:10.200 --> 29:12.868
Nothing else to do,
kind of bored?

29:12.868 --> 29:15.300
"Hey, I know,
let's go gang up on Bailey."

29:15.300 --> 29:16.934
She told me
how you were at the concert.

29:18.734 --> 29:21.634
You ambushed me, okay?
I wasn't expecting her,

29:21.634 --> 29:23.467
and I didn't have dinner.

29:23.467 --> 29:26.100
And, yeah, I had a couple
of drinks. So I was little,

29:26.100 --> 29:28.334
whatever.

29:28.334 --> 29:30.601
I am sorry if I bugged you
or something.

29:32.000 --> 29:34.033
Are we done?

29:34.033 --> 29:35.968
What about Sam?

29:35.968 --> 29:37.767
What about the bottles
that were missing?

29:37.767 --> 29:40.267
Oh. Oh, here we are.

29:40.267 --> 29:41.934
Well, screw that.
I didn't have--

29:41.934 --> 29:44.200
He says you got all weird
when he asked you about it.

29:44.200 --> 29:47.167
Wow. Jule, you would actually
believe him over me?

29:47.167 --> 29:49.467
That-- Wow.
That says a whole hell of a lot

29:49.467 --> 29:51.267
about our relationship.

29:51.267 --> 29:53.234
Look, all I know
is that liquor was missing.

29:53.234 --> 29:55.601
And-- And you have been drinking
an awful lot these days.

29:55.601 --> 29:56.801
So one plus one equals three.

29:56.801 --> 29:58.434
And now all of a sudden
I'm this thief.

29:58.434 --> 30:00.501
Well, you know what?
I don't need this. Okay?

30:00.501 --> 30:02.767
The two of you can take your
stupid ideas about me

30:02.767 --> 30:04.934
and get lost.
We're not gonna leave you.

30:04.934 --> 30:07.667
It's a little late for that,
Sarah.

30:09.300 --> 30:13.334
Bay, we're supposed to not let
each other do stupid things.

30:13.334 --> 30:15.334
Or-- Or self-destructive things.

30:15.334 --> 30:17.000
I mean,
that is the deal with us, right?

30:17.000 --> 30:18.267
That-- That is the job.

30:18.267 --> 30:20.033
Yeah? Well, then you're fired.

30:20.033 --> 30:23.067
Okay, Julia. You're off
the hook. And you too.

30:23.067 --> 30:25.734
No, Bailey. If you're
in some kind of trouble--

30:25.734 --> 30:29.100
I'm not.
And I want you out of here now.

30:31.133 --> 30:32.467
Now!

30:36.834 --> 30:38.934
I am not just dropping this,
Bay.

30:38.934 --> 30:41.200
I am not just forgetting
about this.

30:43.000 --> 30:44.934
[***]

30:57.300 --> 30:59.400
So, what is with her?

30:59.400 --> 31:01.868
Is it this--
This Sam guy she's dating?

31:01.868 --> 31:03.601
Is it this college thing?

31:03.601 --> 31:05.033
I don't know.

31:05.033 --> 31:07.434
'Cause something bit her
in the butt, man.

31:07.434 --> 31:09.133
No kidding.

31:09.133 --> 31:11.634
This is really good food
by the way.

31:11.634 --> 31:14.300
Whoever said there's no such
thing as a free meal?

31:14.300 --> 31:16.434
Any customers come, you're
ditching that. Got it?

31:16.434 --> 31:17.868
Mm.

31:21.033 --> 31:23.334
She's probably driving you
nuts at home, huh?

31:23.334 --> 31:26.133
She can take a number.

31:26.133 --> 31:28.200
The truth is Julia and I
are pretty much

31:28.200 --> 31:29.934
ignoring each other these days.

31:29.934 --> 31:32.734
Good. Good.

31:34.767 --> 31:36.934
I mean that--

31:36.934 --> 31:39.167
That she's not making you too...

31:39.167 --> 31:41.501
No.

31:41.501 --> 31:43.367
She's on my case

31:43.367 --> 31:46.434
all of a sudden now too.

31:47.968 --> 31:50.000
She might say something to you.

31:50.000 --> 31:51.601
About what?

31:52.801 --> 31:54.801
It's so dumb.

31:54.801 --> 31:58.100
She thinks--

31:58.100 --> 32:01.133
She thinks that I'm partying
too much.

32:01.133 --> 32:03.701
Which is so completely
not true.

32:03.701 --> 32:05.200
I mean,

32:05.200 --> 32:08.067
what is freshman year
supposed to be about, right?

32:09.334 --> 32:11.634
Did I ever tell about that--?
That ski trip

32:11.634 --> 32:14.000
that Dudley and I took
Christmas break, freshman year?

32:14.000 --> 32:16.033
Mm-hm.
Let's just say that

32:16.033 --> 32:18.501
it takes a certain amount
of skill to pee Charlie Salinger

32:18.501 --> 32:21.868
in the snow when you've got
five tequila sunrises in you.

32:21.868 --> 32:24.300
[BOTH LAUGHING]

32:24.300 --> 32:26.834
You see?

32:26.834 --> 32:29.567
That's--
That's exactly what I mean.

32:29.567 --> 32:32.901
Not everybody's a straight arrow
like her.

32:32.901 --> 32:34.334
Anyway, whatever, just--

32:34.334 --> 32:35.834
Hey, don't worry about it.

32:35.834 --> 32:38.133
If she said anything
positive for a change,

32:38.133 --> 32:39.534
that would get my attention.

32:39.534 --> 32:41.934
Okay. Cool.

32:44.267 --> 32:46.667
Could you top that off for me?

32:56.267 --> 32:59.300
That's not the right place
for those.

32:59.300 --> 33:00.601
They don't go there.

33:00.601 --> 33:02.234
Oh.

33:09.534 --> 33:11.467
One mistake.

33:11.467 --> 33:12.734
I guess you're fired.

33:12.734 --> 33:14.501
Claudia.

33:16.133 --> 33:18.300
I was...

33:18.300 --> 33:21.534
I might have been a little rough
on you this afternoon.

33:21.534 --> 33:23.701
No harder than I am
on myself most of the time.

33:23.701 --> 33:27.200
But that's-- Anyway,
I shouldn't have gotten so--

33:27.200 --> 33:30.300
It's just if you're gonna do
a job for somebody, you should--

33:33.567 --> 33:36.501
You know,
I would say apology accepted,

33:36.501 --> 33:38.801
except I didn't actually
hear one.

33:38.801 --> 33:41.100
You messed up a huge mailer
for the program.

33:41.100 --> 33:43.400
You cost us time.
You cost us money.

33:45.100 --> 33:47.667
Never mind.

33:47.667 --> 33:51.234
I came there 'cause I wanted
us to be friends.

33:51.234 --> 33:53.534
That's what I was trying to do.

33:55.267 --> 33:57.200
Stupid me.

34:00.767 --> 34:02.534
[CAR BEEPS]

34:04.000 --> 34:05.234
[SCOFFS]

34:05.234 --> 34:07.334
What are you doing?
Stalking him now?

34:07.334 --> 34:08.967
I was waiting for you.

34:08.967 --> 34:11.033
I know you have
that dance class.

34:13.167 --> 34:14.434
What?

34:14.434 --> 34:17.868
Bailey's in trouble, Callie.
He's--

34:17.868 --> 34:19.501
What? Did something happen?
No.

34:19.501 --> 34:21.434
No, nothing happened.

34:21.434 --> 34:23.467
It's just--
God, I mean, you've seen him.

34:23.467 --> 34:26.000
You see him every day.
You have to know.

34:26.000 --> 34:27.266
Know what?

34:28.300 --> 34:29.833
Come on, give me a break.

34:29.833 --> 34:31.567
Callie, you're not blind.

34:32.833 --> 34:35.501
All he does anymore is--
Is get drunk

34:35.501 --> 34:36.833
and be really nasty

34:36.833 --> 34:38.033
and push people away.

34:38.033 --> 34:39.634
It isn't him.
I mean, you saw him.

34:39.634 --> 34:41.801
You know how he was
when you met him.

34:41.801 --> 34:44.033
So what?
This is my influence on him?

34:44.033 --> 34:47.501
You know, I don't need you
insulting me, Sarah. Okay? So--

34:47.501 --> 34:49.100
No. Wait.

34:50.967 --> 34:52.766
Oh, God, d--?

34:52.766 --> 34:56.434
Do you really think
I wanna be here with you?

34:56.434 --> 34:59.767
I mean,
do you have any idea how--?

35:02.167 --> 35:04.467
I'm in love with him.

35:04.467 --> 35:06.868
You know,
I can't help it.

35:06.868 --> 35:09.534
And maybe you are too.
I-I don't-- I don't know.

35:09.534 --> 35:12.200
I don't wanna know.

35:12.200 --> 35:16.367
But I think maybe
I want you to.

35:17.434 --> 35:18.701
What?

35:21.000 --> 35:24.200
Maybe I want you to love him.

35:24.200 --> 35:27.334
You know, 'cause--
'Cause maybe you'll get him

35:27.334 --> 35:29.067
to stop what he's doing.

35:29.067 --> 35:32.634
The drinking and the-- The--

35:32.634 --> 35:35.300
God, I don't even know what.

35:36.667 --> 35:39.000
He won't listen to anybody.

35:39.000 --> 35:41.601
Not Will or Julia

35:41.601 --> 35:43.667
or me.

35:45.567 --> 35:48.000
I gotta go.
Try.

35:49.133 --> 35:51.100
Please.

35:56.968 --> 35:58.968
[DOOR CLOSES]

36:08.767 --> 36:10.701
I'm up.

36:12.067 --> 36:14.067
It's kind of, uh--

36:14.067 --> 36:16.501
Kind of too quiet to sleep.

36:17.801 --> 36:19.133
If you want,
I can go outside,

36:19.133 --> 36:20.634
set off a couple car alarms
for you.

36:20.634 --> 36:23.534
Oh, that's hysterical.

36:26.968 --> 36:29.133
Obviously,
we have a problem.

36:29.133 --> 36:31.701
Only one?

36:31.701 --> 36:33.801
One at a time.

36:36.067 --> 36:37.901
Okay.

36:37.901 --> 36:39.868
Maybe it did happen
too fast.

36:39.868 --> 36:41.601
Us.

36:41.601 --> 36:43.501
This.
I-- I don't think so.

36:43.501 --> 36:45.868
But if you do...

36:47.267 --> 36:49.300
But even if we weren't
living together now,

36:49.300 --> 36:51.901
if, like, six months from now

36:51.901 --> 36:54.334
or a year from now things--

36:54.334 --> 36:57.601
I'm-- I'm stuck here, Grace.

36:57.601 --> 37:00.167
It's not horrible,
you know.

37:00.167 --> 37:03.000
It's an okay place
to be stuck.

37:03.000 --> 37:05.501
But I am.

37:05.501 --> 37:07.868
It's not like I can just
pack up Claudia and Owen

37:07.868 --> 37:09.567
and drag them downtown
to live with you.

37:09.567 --> 37:11.367
That's not--
That's not gonna happen.

37:11.367 --> 37:13.300
See, I-I understand that.

37:13.300 --> 37:15.267
But do you get
why I need to be there?

37:16.434 --> 37:20.033
Uh-uh. Actually, I don't.

37:20.033 --> 37:22.133
I mean,
those people that you help,

37:22.133 --> 37:24.100
they're not gonna be any more
or less homeless

37:24.100 --> 37:25.200
because of where you live.

37:25.200 --> 37:26.767
I'm gonna be different.

37:31.701 --> 37:34.133
Every morning
I would leave my house,

37:34.133 --> 37:36.267
and I would see them right there
in front of me,

37:36.267 --> 37:38.667
how hard it is for them.

37:38.667 --> 37:42.400
I'd know. And they'd see me
and they'd trust me.

37:42.400 --> 37:44.234
It's--

37:44.234 --> 37:46.334
You have to be there to really--

37:48.133 --> 37:49.067
[DOOR OPENS]

37:50.300 --> 37:51.567
Owen, Owen--

37:51.567 --> 37:53.367
No. Wait. Let him.

37:53.367 --> 37:57.033
Let him stay.
He wants to be with you.

37:57.033 --> 37:59.701
I'm gonna sleep
on the couch tonight.

37:59.701 --> 38:01.634
God,
we're back to that again.

38:01.634 --> 38:03.033
No. I just-- I need--

38:03.033 --> 38:05.634
I need to--

38:05.634 --> 38:07.334
I don't know what I need.

38:21.634 --> 38:25.467
Why is Grace
sleeping downstairs?

38:25.467 --> 38:29.434
I don't think
that's any of your business.

38:29.434 --> 38:30.567
Okay.

38:33.100 --> 38:36.834
Something else
I can help you with?

38:36.834 --> 38:39.701
Yeah. Look,
we gotta, uh--

38:39.701 --> 38:42.534
Something bad's going on
with Bay.

38:42.534 --> 38:43.634
[SCOFFS]

38:43.634 --> 38:46.133
Oh, yeah?
What would that be?

38:46.133 --> 38:48.300
What's the attitude?

38:48.300 --> 38:50.767
No. Go ahead.
Tell me all about it.

38:50.767 --> 38:53.934
Wow. Charlie, we can't even
have a conversation anymore?

38:53.934 --> 38:56.634
Oh, sure. Now.

38:56.634 --> 38:58.834
What about when I've been
trying to talk to you for--

38:58.834 --> 39:00.033
For, like, weeks.

39:00.033 --> 39:01.734
And all you would do is--
Is blow me off

39:01.734 --> 39:03.200
or run off to Sam's.

39:03.200 --> 39:04.901
And the way you've
been treating Grace,

39:04.901 --> 39:06.734
I don't know why I should
talk to you at all.

39:06.734 --> 39:08.467
Look, that's all--

39:08.467 --> 39:11.234
You know what,
this isn't about me.

39:11.234 --> 39:12.767
This is about Bailey.

39:12.767 --> 39:14.801
And how he's partying
too much.

39:16.367 --> 39:17.901
You know about it?

39:17.901 --> 39:19.934
Why don't you just admit
that you can't stand

39:19.934 --> 39:21.834
seeing somebody else
enjoying themselves.

39:21.834 --> 39:23.968
What?

39:23.968 --> 39:26.133
That is so not--
Let me give you a news flash,

39:26.133 --> 39:28.801
Julia, you're not the smartest
person in the world.

39:28.801 --> 39:30.767
You don't know everything.

39:30.767 --> 39:33.100
Neither do you.

39:35.067 --> 39:36.667
[DOOR SLAMS]

39:37.801 --> 39:41.067
[SLOW ROCK MUSIC
PLAYING ON RADIO]

39:46.367 --> 39:49.367
What you reading?

39:49.367 --> 39:51.767
I have no idea.

39:51.767 --> 39:54.667
 <i>* I believe</i>
 <i>In right and wrong *</i>

39:54.667 --> 39:57.000
So.

39:57.000 --> 39:59.234
Dare I ask?

40:01.000 --> 40:03.367
Rent money?

40:03.367 --> 40:05.300
Not yet.

40:08.267 --> 40:11.601
You kicking me out?

40:11.601 --> 40:12.901
Joining the growing numbers

40:12.901 --> 40:16.367
of the "I Hate Bailey Club"?

40:16.367 --> 40:19.934
Yeah, well, you are kind of
a pain in the ass sometimes.

40:23.667 --> 40:26.100
Not all the time,
though.

40:27.834 --> 40:30.601
Huh?

40:30.601 --> 40:31.834
Hm?

40:31.834 --> 40:34.200
Come on, say it.

40:34.200 --> 40:36.567
Not all the time.

40:36.567 --> 40:38.334
Okay. Good.

40:38.334 --> 40:40.767
I have one friend.

40:42.067 --> 40:43.734
I'm gonna grab a beer.
You want?

40:43.734 --> 40:46.634
No, thanks. I'll pass.

40:48.634 --> 40:52.300
You know,
maybe you ought to pass too.

40:54.167 --> 40:57.501
That's all you need, you know.

40:57.501 --> 40:59.200
What? Beer?

40:59.200 --> 41:01.701
No.

41:01.701 --> 41:04.300
One good friend.

41:04.300 --> 41:06.267
[CHUCKLES]

41:09.067 --> 41:10.801
That's you, Cal.

41:14.434 --> 41:16.801
My one good friend.

41:18.467 --> 41:20.100
Yeah?

41:21.033 --> 41:22.667
Yeah.

41:26.601 --> 41:28.567
Come on.

41:28.567 --> 41:30.334
Leave that.

41:30.334 --> 41:32.100
Let's go to bed.

41:36.567 --> 41:38.901
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

41:38.901 --> 41:40.834
[***]

41:55.200 --> 41:57.200
Hey.

41:58.534 --> 42:02.234
Looks like I wasn't
the big draw after all.

42:07.501 --> 42:09.567
Look at that.

42:09.567 --> 42:11.601
See.

42:11.601 --> 42:13.501
He wanted you.

42:16.901 --> 42:18.734
I, um--

42:20.400 --> 42:23.934
I know you're kind of big
on being needed, Grace.

42:23.934 --> 42:28.267
And I know you get
that in your work a lot.

42:28.267 --> 42:31.634
But that's not
the only place where--

42:31.634 --> 42:33.434
Us too, you know?

42:35.434 --> 42:38.934
We need you here.

42:38.934 --> 42:42.434
Please.

42:42.434 --> 42:45.334
Stay.

42:55.300 --> 42:56.901
Okay.

42:58.467 --> 43:00.934
Good.

43:00.934 --> 43:02.834
Good.

43:05.834 --> 43:08.467
Watch.
Don't wake him.

43:10.000 --> 43:12.200
Be careful.

43:12.200 --> 43:14.234
Are we gonna fit?

43:14.234 --> 43:16.367
We'll make room.

43:29.801 --> 43:31.868
